.row-eq-height {
  display: -webkit-box;
  display: -webkit-flex;
  display: -ms-flexbox;
  display:         flex;
}

The .row-eq-height class uses CSS3's flexbox layout mode, which is not supported in Internet Explorer 9 and below.

In any unsupported browser, the .row-eq-height class will have no effect.
